Congratulations on joining the Lost Alley Coffee Syndicate, an organisation dedicated to
promoting coffee literacy. It is your responsibility to build out their cloud infrastructure, securely
and reliably.
Your first task has arrived and it is to deploy the application that is described below.

Architecture
The application consists of:
● A backend API served over HTTP .
● The API stack is written in Typescript using Express.js.
● Data is stored in a flatfile database on the local disk.
● Development is in the early stages and the app is yet to follow a monolithic or microservice
approach.
The goals of the task are:
● The solution scales to demand. There are a small-but-growing number of API users and
they are all located within Australia.
● It is highly available and performant.
● Solution is secure and cost effective.
● The deployment process is relatively simple and allows for fast deployment.
● Consider how the data could be stored and managed differently as the app scales.
Please present how you would approach this task and what considerations would need to be made
when building this solution.

Hands on
The first iteration of the app is complete, and the source code (including an uploaded Docker
image) is available at https://github.com/medipass/coffee-dictionary. Based on the requirements
above, prepare to show us how you would deploy the application to AWS. The app does not
require an external database, and therefore it is not necessary to deploy a database server. The
solution should be pseudo code - avoid spending your money creating real resources in AWS.
Only spend as much time as you feel comfortable doing so - ideally up to an hour. We're looking at
a practical demonstration of your ability to use AWS and you're open to approach the challenge
how you see fit. There is no need to complete all the requirements, however, later when we chat
about the strengths and weaknesses of the solution, we'll ask you to evaluate the gaps too.
